hadith.english-text:
It was narrated that Ibn 'Abbas said: "A man said: 'O
Messenger of Allah! My father has died and he did not perform Hajj;
shall I perform Hajj on his behalf?' He said: 'Don't you think that
if your father owed a debt you would pay it off?' The man said:
'Yes.' He said: 'The debt owed to Allah is more deserving (of being
paid off)."'
